                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760c.61/162b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="16" xml:id="d527fn16">A similar telegram was sent on the
                        same date to the Chargé in Japan with instructions to “repeat textually to
                        Peking and summarize to Vladivostok and Harbin” (file no.
                        760c.61/162a).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following American note delivered to Italian Embassy this afternoon and given to
                    press for release morning papers August 11th. <pb facs="0569" n="469"
                        xml:id="pg_469"/> Repeat textually to Paris, Rome, Berlin, Prague and
                    Warsaw. Send full summary to other European missions and to Helsingfors, Riga,
                    Tiflis and Constantinople. Latter for transmission to McCully, Sevastopol.
                    Instruct in all cases to give fullest possible publicity:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of note printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
